<recipe lang="en-uk" xmlns:lxslt="http://xml.apache.org/xslt">
<title><![CDATA[Arancine, Classic version]]></title>
<description><![CDATA[If made from scratch and from risotto leftovers, this is the classic recipe. There is a XIII century Bahgdad coockbook with a similar dish called naranjiya. They freeze well.]]></description>
<source/>
<img></img>
<cuisine>
<style>Italian</style>
<region>Sicilian</region>
<approach/>
</cuisine>
<tags>
<tag>Snack</tag>
</tags>
<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step><![CDATA[Put the rice ingredients in a pot, bring to boil, then lower heat and cover tightly until stock absorbed, 20 mins]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Remove from fire, spoon in egg and cheese, then spread on platter to cool]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Make the filling: sautè onion for 7 mins]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add beef and rosemary, sauté until seared, then sweat with white wine until evaporated.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Add passata or canned tomatoes broken with a fork, peas, and lower the heat (medium low for canned tomatoes, low for passata). Cook until quite thick then cool.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Roll 1/12 of the rice into a ball, leaving an indentation. Fill it with the ragú and wrap the rice around it to close the ball. Roll ball in flour, then beatn egg, then breadcrumb.]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Deep fry at 180°C. Serve warm or room temperature]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
